						               													<description>&amp;quot;Card game for 2 players. The action takes place in the world of Virtual World of Tron.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One player represents Tron and the other plays as the Master Control Program or MCP. Each player uses a separate custom deck of cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Tron deck is made up of six types of cards: Programs (Characters), Skill (used to defeat Games and Security), Escape (used to go Rogue), Activation (used to become Activated), Transport (used to reach the Mesa), and Sub-Routines (various effects).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The MCP deck has four types of cards: Control (required to win the game), Games (used to destroy Programs on the Game Grid), Security (used to destroy Programs off the Game Grid), and Sub-Routines (various effects).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The MCP player wins when all ten Control cards have been downloaded (put into play). Tron wins by Derezzing (destroying) the MCP in Program Delete Phase.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
